g.text: T1 | 4KB Data Block | User Payload (Block N)
T4 | 4KB Data Apply | Block N Final Location
T5 | 4KB Meta Apply | Inode Table + Bitmap Final
T1 | 4KB Data Write | Direct to Data Block N
T3 | 4KB Meta Jnl | Journal Inode + Bitmap
T5 | 4KB Meta Apply | Inode Table + Bitmap Final
If crash happens mid-write, the journal contains the ACTUAL DATA. Zero data loss for committed txns.
fsync(fd); // Ensure data is on platter
Metadata is always valid. Crash may leave file with OLD data but NEW size/mtime if not fsync'd.
Trade-off: 40% Lower Write I/O vs. Data Integrity
